<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="556" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,358,1319]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1150,1175]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[324,448,1150,1175]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Flexocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[324,448,1150,1175]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="556">Flexocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by its robust appearance, face with black spots mesad of lateral frontal sutures; crown and pronotum finely rugose; frontoclypeus and anteclypeus distinctly elevated; genae lateral margin concave in middle; anteclypeus apex broad, surpassing apex of gena; style apex pointed, sickle-shaped, ventral margin toothlike at apical half, usually without setae; aedeagal shaft S-shaped or arched, with at least 
<number box="[1422,1436,1259,1283]" pageId="1" pageNumber="556" value="2.0">2</number>
processes, dorsal apodeme developed, usually bifurcate apically.
</paragraph>
